{"type":"text","timestamp":1780204725971,"sessionID":"ses_1838ab765ffeDkoguY5zw44Q55","part":{"id":"prt_e7c7836f5001Lfxma3OVefy6BF","messageID":"msg_e7c782d47001cNLwdMJTHWebgf","sessionID":"ses_1838ab765ffeDkoguY5zw44Q55","type":"text","text":"---\n\n# Iteration 2 — Lane C Orchestrator + Harness Correctness\n\n## Focus\n\nDim C orchestrator (`run-skill-benchmark.cjs`) and harness scripts (`contamination-lint.cjs`, `advisor-probe.cjs`, `build-report.cjs`, `_args.cjs`). Five axes: malformed-fixture degradation, contamination banned-vocab breadth, advisor-probe spawn/timeout/rank math, build-report anti-drift, arg parsing.\n\n---\n\n## Findings\n\n### P0 — Correctness / Crash\n\n**P0-F1 | contamination-lint.cjs:46-47**\n- **Issue:** `seg` is `const` inside the for-of block scope; referenced outside that scope on line 47: `if (seg && seg.length > 3) tokens.add(seg);`. This is a `ReferenceError` that fires for ANY resource path whose segments include any token > 3 characters.\n- **Fix:** Move the length check inside the loop body: `for (const seg of resourcePath.split('/')) { if (seg.length > 3) tokens.add(seg); }`\n\n---\n\n**P0-F2 | run-skill-benchmark.cjs:54**\n- **Issue:** `priv = fs.existsSync(privPath) ? JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(privPath, 'utf8')) : { expected: {} }` — the `JSON.parse` executes as the truthy branch of the ternary, meaning it is NOT inside the `try` block. A malformed private fixture throws uncaught, crashing the entire run with `TypeError: Cannot read property 'expected' of undefined`.\n- **Fix:** Move private fixture loading inside the `try` block alongside the public load.\n\n---\n\n**P0-F3 | advisor-probe.cjs:35**\n- **Issue:** `String(prompt || '')` where prompt could be `undefined` produces `\"undefined\"` CLI arg; also `timeoutMs` parameter is accepted but never forwarded at the call site in run-skill-benchmark.cjs:113-115.\n- **Fix:** Use `String(prompt ?? '')` and explicitly pass `timeoutMs: 60000` at the call site.\n\n---\n\n### P1 — Degraded / Incomplete / Missing Validation\n\n**P1-F4 | score-skill-benchmark.cjs:65-66**\n- **Issue:** `expected.resources` being `undefined` (not `[]`) causes all resources to be counted as wasted (D3=0) while D2/D1-intra give 1 for negative scenarios — scoring inconsistency.\n- **Fix:** Normalize `expected.resources ?? []` at the top of `scoreScenario`.\n\n---\n\n**P1-F5 | score-skill-benchmark.cjs:73**\n- **Issue:** `routed === 0` produces `Math.max(0, 1 - 0/0)` = `NaN`. This propagates into `measured` and corrupts `modeAScore`.\n- **Fix:** The guard `routed === 0` at line 73 exists but the NaN path is reachable; ensure the zero-routing branch returns 1 before any division.\n\n---\n\n**P1-F6 | advisor-probe.cjs:68**\n- **Issue:** For `negative=true`, `rank > 5` success allows skill at rank 6 as pass; skill at rank 5 scores 0. The boundary should be `> 3` (absent or barely in recommendations = success for negative).\n- **Fix:** Use `rank > 3` for negative success, or 0.5 for rank 4-5 as marginal leak.\n\n---\n\n**P1-F7 | run-skill-benchmark.cjs:71 / _args.cjs**\n- **Issue:** `_args.cjs` requires `--advisor-mode=value` syntax; bare `--advisor-mode python` is treated as boolean `true`; string `\"false\"` or `\"0\"` is truthy but not `'python'`, so probe silently skipped.\n- **Fix:** Document `=value` requirement; add explicit falsy-string handling.\n\n---\n\n### P2 — Style / Naming / Docs\n\n**P2-F8 | build-report.cjs:18**\n- **Issue:** `d.status || 'unscored'` renders `_undefined_` if status is the literal string `\"undefined\"` in JSON.\n- **Fix:** Use `d.status ?? 'unscored'` (nullish coalescing).\n\n---\n\n**P2-F9 | contamination-lint.cjs:29**\n- **Issue:** `trigger_phrases:` regex requires no blank line between key and list items; blank line silently produces zero triggers.\n- **Fix:** Document blank-line-free requirement; add warning if trigger_phrases block exists but yields no triggers.\n\n---\n\n**P2-F10 | contamination-lint.cjs:57**\n- **Issue:** `add()` drops tokens with `trim().length <= 2`; could miss 2-3 char skill ids like `sk`, `py` as contamination.\n- **Fix:** Lower threshold to `> 1`; document the false-positive avoidance rationale.\n\n---\n\n## Verdict\n\n**Review verdict: CONDITIONAL**\n\nTwo P0 crashes (P0-F1 `seg` scope bug, P0-F2 uncaught private fixture parse) and one P0 (P0-F3 prompt undefined) exist. P0-F1 and P0-F2 would crash any real run against a skill with resources. P1-F5 (NaN in D3) can corrupt aggregate scoring for zero-routing scenarios. Three P1s degrade correctness of advisor-based scoring and negative-scenario handling. The P2s are minor. The harness is structurally sound in design but has three crash bugs that would fire on normal inputs — these must be fixed before the Lane C CI gate is reliable.","time":{"start":1780204713717,"end":1780204725967}}}
